===subject:response to Keri Zink
===from:Keith Lewis
===date:Tue Oct  8 20:22:39 2002
===message:The World War I soliders portrayed in "All Quiet On The Western Front" denied the necessity of war.  Through satire, they oversimplified the causes of the war and took a stand for pacifism.  I agree that many innocent men died-men who did not care about the assasination of some leader in some other country thousands of miles from home.  They did however, care about the German agression towards innocent people, specifically the sinking of the Lusatania.  The United States, if not the soilders, cared about the note sent to Mexico from Zimmerman promising a requsition of Texas lost in the 19th Century.  The Americans of that time tried to preserve a neutral attitude, but were forced into the fight.  I agree with your statment that pacifism will never prevent war.  The hope is that we can possably prevent large-scale wars such as WWI and WWII.  The enforcement of policy and human rights will have to continue to preserve justice and faith in the United Nations.
=========yorg=========
===subject:Lost Peace
===from:Wendy Abdo
