===message:The need for power can be a determining factor in the origin of wars. Hitler is a great example of this concept. He led the German people into a war that he had been dreaming about for sometime. Hitler wanted Germany to be the greatest, largest power in the world. In order for this dream to come true, Hitler had to lead Germany into WWII so Germany could gain more power by defeating other countries. If this had occured, Hitler could have imposed his will and forced countries, such as Britain and France, to follow his direction.
